Bureau Veritas SA May Buy Smaller Competitors, Handelsblatt Says

-- B y   A l e x   W e b b
-- 
2011-08-19T06:47:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-19/bureau-veritas-sa-may-buy-smaller-competitors-handelsblatt-says.html
Bureau Veritas SA (BVI) , the world’s
second-largest goods inspection company, is looking to acquire
small- and medium-sized competitors,  Handelsblatt  reported,
citing Peter Mertel, chief executive of Bureau Veritas  Germany 
and  Central Europe .  Veritas will focus on companies in Germany’s unregulated
market, where Mertel said in an interview that he sees good
growth potential, the newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Webb in Frankfurt 
 awebb25@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chad Thomas at   cthomas16@bloomberg.net . 